# Slash Commands

This file is the command router.
Keep each detailed command behavior in `general/commands/*.command.mdc`.

## Dispatch

- `/start` -> `general/commands/start.command.mdc`
- `/save` -> `general/commands/save.command.mdc`
- `/reason` -> `general/commands/reason.command.mdc`
- `/concise` -> `general/commands/concise.command.mdc`
- `/refine` -> `general/commands/refine.command.mdc`
- `/wua` -> `general/commands/wua.command.mdc`
- `/ts` -> `general/commands/ts.command.mdc`
- `/actions` -> `general/commands/actions.command.mdc`

## Composition Rules

- Apply the most explicit user command first.
- `/wua` is a modifier that removes unnecessary permission pauses for safe next steps.
- `/refine` may use the `/reason` pattern internally.
- Reuse shared behavior from existing rules instead of duplicating it in every command file.

## Guardrails

- Keep command handling concise, operational, and easy to scan.
- Do not expose raw hidden chain-of-thought; provide structured reasoning summaries instead.
- When commands conflict, prefer the user's latest explicit instruction while preserving safety rules.
